<BaseLayout title="About">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>About</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="about-content">
    <p>
      I'm Josh Friedman. I build custom business systems — websites, dashboards, automations, data pipelines — using AI, in days instead of months, at a fraction of what agencies charge. When I'm done, you own everything and can run it yourself.
    </p>

    <p>
      The path here wasn't linear. I started in creative production and brand strategy, then co-founded a design studio in LA where we built brands and campaigns for Fox Searchlight, HBO, and the Elizabeth Taylor Trust. I led product at a social Q&A platform called AnyQuestion, which was acquired by WHOOP — where I spent the next several years leading Product Marketing.
    </p>

    <p>
      Along the way I became obsessed with a question: what happens when AI stops being a tool you use and starts being a medium you build with? The answer changed everything about how I work. I built an AI-powered operating system for my own life — an agentic workflow that handles meeting capture, task management, research, writing, and analysis. Not as a side project. As the way I actually work, every day.
    </p>

    <p>
      That system — and the thinking behind it — became the foundation for what I do now. I help people and teams see their work differently, then rebuild it. The system is the proof. The insight is the offering.
    </p>

    <h2>What I believe</h2>

    <p>
      Software isn't something you buy. It's something you can build. The tools got that good. An invoice pipeline that saves 15 hours a week, a custom dashboard that replaces three SaaS subscriptions, a website that's live in a week instead of three months — these aren't hypotheticals. They're Tuesday.
    </p>

    <p>
      The moat isn't technical. The moat is knowing <em>what</em> to build — domain judgment that no tool provides — and transferring the capability so you're not dependent on anyone, including me.
    </p>

    <h2>This site</h2>

    <p>
      This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, deployed on <a href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</a>, and written in markdown. The <a href="/changelog">changelog</a> is a running feed of what I'm building, thinking, and shipping. Not a portfolio. A living document.
    </p>

    <div class="about-links">
